title: Netanyahu slams Palestinian Authority for denying that Hamas carried out massacre at Israeli music festival
description: Israel Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu slammed the Palestinian Authority for claiming that Hamas was not responsible for the Oct. 7 massacre.

title: Taylor Swift returns to Rio stage after postponing Eras Tour concert, fan death
description: Taylor Swift resumed The Eras Tour in Brazil after canceling concert on Nov. 18 due to record heatwave across Rio. One fan died Friday after fainting outside stadium.

title: Javier Milei crushes Argentine left, becomes world's first libertarian head of state
description: Argentina headed to the polls tonight in a tight election between two very distinct candidates: libertarian economist Javier Milei, and current Peronist Economy Minister Sergio Massa.

title: NYT editorial board acknowledges the harms of COVID school closures: All of this was 'predicted in real time'
description: 'The Big Weekend Show' co-hosts react to a New York Times op-ed about the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on student learning loss.

title: NYC dogwalker with high hopes artwork would sell for millions has dreams dashed: report
description: A former New York City dog walker who fell into ownership of a Chuck Close artwork had high hopes on mushrooms he could sell the piece for eight figures, but it sold for much less.

title: Aaron Nola inks 7-year deal to stay with Phillies
description: Aaron Nola could have been one of the pitchers on the move in the offseason, but the Philadelphia Phillies star is staying put. He inked a new 7-year deal Sunday.

title: California Gov. Gavin Newsom announces 10 Freeway reopening is ahead of schedule
description: California Gov. Gavin Newsom announced on Sunday that the 10 Freeway closure in downtown Los Angeles is ahead of schedule and could open sooner than projected.

title: Heidi Klum struts topless at F1 in Las Vegas; joins Brad Pitt, Justin Bieber at Grand Prix
description: Heidi Klum showed some skin for wild night out after joining Rihanna, David Beckham and Paris Hilton at star-studded Formula One Grand Prix in Las Vegas, Nevada.

title: ‘Shock therapy’ libertarian candidate Javier Milei, who ran as outsider, wins Argentine presidential election
description: Javier Milei, a libertarian outsider candidate who has been compared to Donald Trump, has been elected as the next president of Argentina.

title: Bills' Taylor Rapp leaves game in ambulance after suffering scary neck injury
description: Buffalo Bills safety Taylor Rapp suffered a neck injury during Sunday's game against the New York Jets and was taken away in an ambulance.

title: Bills put struggles in the rearview for blowout win over Jets
description: Josh Allen and the Buffalo Bills put all of the criticism behind them on Sunday night with a 32-6 drubbing of the New York Jets. Allen had three touchdown passes.

title: Rams come up clutch in 4th quarter to squeak past Seahawks
description: The Los Angeles Rams rallied to pull off a come back against the Seattle Seahawks. Lucas Havrisik made a 22-yard field goal with under 2 minutes to play

title: Chargers' Brandon Staley snaps at reporter over question about defensive play-calling
description: Los Angeles Chargers head coach Brandon Staley fired back at a reporter on Sunday after a question about the team's defense following the loss to the Green Bay Packers.

title: Rotten apple: New York dubbed 'least free state' in country in new study
description: New York ranked as "least free state" with high taxes and debt, according to a new study.

title: Chargers' Joey Bosa in tears after suffering foot injury in loss to Packers
description: Los Angeles Chargers talented edge rusher Joey Bosa was in tears on a medical cart at Lambeau Field on Sunday after injuring his foot against the Green Bay Packers.

title: 49ers take down Buccaneers as Christian McCaffrey finds the end zone once more
description: Christian McCaffrey found the end zone once again, while Brandon Aiyuk set a new career-high in receiving yards as the San Francisco 49ers took down the Tampa Bay Buccaneers.
